Job Details
Our client, a multinational Automotive company is seeking a Network Development Manager
.
You will be directly reporting to the Dealer Development Director Mission and main challenges
To analyse, develop and consult the dealer network and Company&apos;s
Middle East on the best possible market exploitation for existing and new markets through adequate facilities, management selection and development and process implementationTo ensure brand adequate dealership appearance in terms of exterior and interior Corporate Identity and architectural conceptsTo initiate, co-ordinate and consult in business process improvement in the dealershipsTo ensure the implementation of Company&apos;s
standards in the dealer networkResponsibilitiesTasks and CustomersMain Tasks (relating products, services ...) Co-ordination of on-site consultancy programs, eg VSAP Deployment of consultants to the markets Co-ordination of activities with the Company&apos;s ME business units Review of targets and achievements and follow up actions Supporting the Dealer Management Selection and training programs Coordination of assessment centers and psychometric tests Assisting in the developing of training activities to increase knowledge on dealer management level in co-ordination with Company&apos;s ME training staff.
Business Management Co-ordination of business plans for the NearMiddle East countries Analysis of business plans with the partner Definition of measures to increase profitability in conjunction with business unitsBonus Margin System Co ordinate with Dealers and Company&apos;s ME staff to ensure full understanding of BMS programme.
Ensure performance relating to sales vs target, CSS and focus areas is understood and plans in place to achieve targets. Development and implementation of dealer standards and organization structure Development of dealerships towards the fulfillment of standards Co-ordination with the Company&apos;s ME business units Audit of dealer standardsConsultation of dealers in facility planning and enhancement Planning of new showrooms and after sales facilities Co-ordination of all plans with
Middle East business units and dealership Guiding the dealer in terms of necessary investments based on business cases Project management support for major building projectsKPIs (Network coverage and exclusivity of facilities, dealer standard fulfillment, no. of assessments, Dealer Satisfaction Index, return on sales per dealer, CSS scores, VSAP performance scores, budget control.
Requirements
Knowledge, Skills and Abilities required good automotive industry knowledge, strong analytical skills, resilience, assertiveness, systematic, good communication skills, flexible, confident, success orientated, customer orientated and diligent with good attention to detail and proactive skills.Desired Qualification Bachelor degree in business administrationDesired Experience 5 years automotive industry experience preferably in overseas markets with sales andor aftersales experience, working with automotive industry KPIs, project management experience, adapting and implementing strategies to operational levelThe holder of the position is responsible for hisher own actions within the framework of the duties assigned to himher. In fulfilling the requirements of the job description, heshe will also be expected to perform tasks which, due to their irregular occurrence, are not included in the job description but which by their nature are part of the job. Heshe is entitled to request information about the tasks assigned to himher from hisher superior. Heshe must report significant events occurring within hisher area of responsibility to hisher superior without prompting and must provideobtain the inter-functional information necessary for ensuring efficient completion of tasks.
